<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,620,899]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,656,683]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Distribution.</emphasis>
Thus far only known from 
<collectingCountry box="[667,743,657,683]" name="France" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">France</collectingCountry>
and Britain. 
<collectingCountry box="[893,992,657,683]" name="Portugal" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: two provinces, Minho (this study) and Baixo Alentejo (
<bibRefCitation author="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M." box="[335,588,692,719]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="125 - 137" refId="ref33294" refString="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M. (2015) Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from the Iberian Peninsula, with description of three new species. Zootaxa, 3964 (1), 125 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3964.1.9" type="journal article" year="2015">Naglis &amp; Barták 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,620,899]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,729,755]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Ecology.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[309,408,729,755]" name="Portugal" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: on the beach at Esposende (Minho), it was collected in a site with littoral rocks, muddy patches and among marine vegetation on the beach. Elsewhere in Europe, it is found on littoral rocks, often in sheltered sites (Martin Drake, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,620,899]" box="[199,513,836,863]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,836,863]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
